<br>
I dislike the stressing atmosphere of PoP, selling your soul or your mother to get a good group, etc. I hope LoY will be somewhere inbetween old world and PoP, id est, xpable by 61+ even if less profitable xpwise as PoP-zones.<br>
<br>
PoP has another downside : it creates &quot;dungeon&quot; and &quot;knowledge&quot; newbies. Some low 50s start to xp exclusively in PoP zones as the xp rate is just not comparable to any other zone. They stick in tier 1 planes till level 60, and than start the usual path, Valor-Storms tier 2 and so on.<br>
<br>
Now they level much faster than other low 50s but are stuck, till level 60, to 4 zones : PoD, PoI, PoJ, PoN. And they don't go to other zones, they never go into a dungeon, they miss a lot about aggro management and crowd control (all these zones are pure outdoor zones though PoJ and factory are somewhere inbetween) deep under the earth in the dungeons of our youth when life starts at 51.<br>
<br>
Result, you get some 63+ players who jumped from 53 to 63 within a couple of weeks (well, a bit more), and are totally lost outside of the planes. They don't know their way through many zones, they don't know the major cities of Norrath/Luclin, heck I even met a 62 cleric who was unable to go from Nexus to Fungus Grove and later explained he never had HEARD about FG ! And that cleric was not an e-bay character...<br>
<br>
This is not the worst part (after all, lacking of game culture is not a crime), but this often goes with a lack of game mechanisms, because if you level too fast in the same 4 zones + 2 (Valor/Storms) past 60, you miss a lot about tacticts, strategy, adaptation of play technics in relation to zone/mob. And this can become dangerous in dungeons on raids. Sure, any PoP mob hits as hard or harder than many dungeon mobs, but a mob is not HARD because it hits hard. There are many other factors which make a mob difficult, capacity of single pulling, aoes, hps, aggro specificities, spell casting ability, resists, layout of the dungeon, pathing bugs, etc etc.<br>
<br>
These players all missed that and did not use a progressive learning curve, which results in a certain unexperience and therefore increased danger in raid situations.<br>
<br>
Well, let's see how LoY will be !<br>
<br>
Elemental Greetings<br>
<br>
Adonhiram<br>
62 Archmage<br>
AB<br>
