<br>
1. Un-nerf the /consider system.  What idiot thought this up anyway?  Way to completely lock a person out from 95% of the content.<br>
<br>
2. Adjust the ZEM for specific zones.  Gojirax makes a good case for CT, and I'm sure we all can come up with a list of zones that should be good xp for 60+.<br>
<br>
The point is that until we're out of this funnel -- concentrating more and more players into a smaller and smaller number of zones -- the game will be overcrowded and ultimately not hold enough interest for the players.  <br>
<br>
I'm beginning to feel like pre-Kunark... &quot;Oh hey, want to go to lguk, solb, or do seafuries?&quot;  Now that was fine at the time, but things have changed in EQ since then. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eandori>Eandori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 570<br> <font color=#333333>(2/7/03 11:37:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=191.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rate of EXP gain in POP zones vs non-POP zones</span><hr size=1> Did I predict this coming or what? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Master Eandori Raintree<br>
